{"word":"γενέτης","slug":"γενέτης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γενέτης</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>(I.1.) from <a href='S:γείνομαι'><el>γείνομαι</el></a>; (I.2.) from <a href='S:γίγνομαι'><el>γίγνομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>the begetter, father, ancestor</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, and in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>parents</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the begotten, the son</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, = <el>γενέθλιοι θεοί</el>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}